==English==

===Etymology===
Probably from {{etyl|non|en}} {{term|slyngja|lang=non}}, {{term|slyngva|lang=non||to hurl}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*slingwaną||to worm, twist}} (compare Old English {{term|slingan|lang=ang||to wind, twist}}, German {{term|schlingen|lang=de||to swing, wind, twist}}, Danish {{term|slynge|lang=da}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*slenk||to turn, twist}} (compare Welsh {{term|llyngyr|lang=cy||worms, maggots}}, Lithuanian {{term|sliñkti|lang=lt||to crawl like a snake}}, Latvian {{term|slìkt|lang=lv||to sink}}).

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈslɪŋ/}}
* {{a|US|also}} {{IPA|/ˈsliːŋ/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪŋ}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|slings|slinging|'''[[slung]]''' or '''[[slang]]'''|slung}}

# To [[throw]] with a circular or arcing motion.
